BST all year would: 
> save energy;
> prevent accidents (lighter evenings - see https://www.rospa.com/road-safety/advice/road-users/british-summertime-fact-sheet/);
> promote outdoor leisure activity;
> be good for the economy; and
> “save almost 500,000 tonnes of CO2 each year, equivalent to taking 185,000 cars off the road permanently” 
> greatly reduce the number of fatalities on Britain's roads (https://1010uk.org/lighterlater); and 
> overall lead to greater happiness.

